  "texts": [
    "Recall that the complexified cotangent bundle can be decomposed asT * Σ C = T * Σ ⊗ C = K Σ ⊕ KΣ, where K Σ is the canonical bundle.",
    "There is a corresponding decomposition of Sym 2 (T * Σ) C as K 2 Σ ⊕K Σ KΣ ⊕ K2 Σ.",
    "Given a real symmetric tensor α ∈ Sym 2 (T * B), let α C = α 2,0 + α 1,1 + α 0,2 be the decomposition of its complex-linear extension into these components.",
    "Then, α is conformal to ǧ ∈ c if and only if α = α 1,1.",
    "Since α is real, α 2,0 = α 0,2, hence α = α 1,1 if and only if α 2,0 = 0."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}